r C. Clarke.  It was pretty good, but got kinda goofy at the end.  He also wrote the 2001 series.  2001 = good.  2010 = good too.  2061 = decent.  3001 = Makes you want to hire a hitman to kill the person who published it since it's total crap.<br>
<br>
Oh, the Dark Tower series by Stephen King rocks.  It's up there with the Foundation and Lord of the Rings series as the best series I've ever read.<br>
<br>
Ender's Game series was cool, until the end where like RAMA it got all wierd.  Seems like they had a good thing, but should've just ended instead of making up some dumb means for solving everything.<br>
<br>
Hmm..   the Dune series was great until like the 4th book.  Then it got all stupid too in my opinion.  It just seems like too many series start out with a great idea, but then draw it out longer than they really should.  <br>
<br>
As for cool stuff to read that isn't Sci-Fi, 'Lord of the Flies' is great, and 'Of Mice and Men' is also a wonderful book, though it's about the saddest thing I've ever read.  One summer I got into a literature kick and started reading a lot of books people claim to be great literature or whatever since I wanted to see why everyone wanted people to learn about them in class and junk. <br>
<br>
Oh oh...  '1984' has the best ending I've ever read in any book.  If you haven't read it, you should just because the last sentence is so awesome. <p>Sbik Swashbucklugget<br>
